<paragraph id="F20E36F7A267FFBEFF2D69C23F615459" blockId="11.[167,780,731,2091]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFF2D69C23F6158C5" bold="true" box="[168,330,1183,1207]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">Identification.</emphasis>
Plants 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFE1E69C23FC658C5" box="[411,493,1183,1207]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 cm</quantity>
high; herbaceous; caespitose. Taproots and rhizomes present. Stems 1.0– 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFD3A699C3D2158AB" box="[703,778,1217,1241]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="cm" value="3.5">3.5 cm</quantity>
long; erect or ascending; hairy, with simple and branched hairs (2–5 rays: 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFEE6685B3F5F596F" box="[355,372,1286,1309]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">T</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFE01685B3FBC596F" box="[388,407,1286,1309]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFE22685B3F90596F" box="[423,443,1286,1309]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14792" name="Yale University" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Herbarium">Y</collectionCode>
, cruciform, ternate, and dendritic). Leaves basal; alternate or whorled; petiolate or subsessile. Petioles 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFE0568143FF05913" box="[384,475,1353,1377]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 mm</quantity>
long; winged; margins ciliate, with simple hairs. Leaf blades 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFDD268363CEE59F1" box="[599,709,1387,1411]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="3.0">3–12 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFF2D68D03F0059D7" box="[168,299,1421,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="2.5999999999999996" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="1.4">1.4–3.8 mm</quantity>
wide; obtrullate or oblanceolate; bases attenuate; abaxial and adaxial surfaces both moderately to densely hairy, with simple and branched hairs (2–5 rays: 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFF2D68A93E975A79" box="[168,188,1524,1547]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14792" name="Yale University" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Herbarium">Y</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFF4368A93EF25A79" box="[198,217,1524,1547]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
, ternate, and dendritic); margins ciliate, with simple hairs; apices obtuse. Inflorescence a corymbose raceme, with 2–4 flowers; not elongating as the fruit matures or slightly elongating as the fruit matures. Pedicels 1.5–6.0 mm long; hairy. Sepals 4; 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFE426B263C635AE1" box="[455,584,1659,1683]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.4">2.4–3.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFD086B263D215AE1" box="[653,778,1659,1683]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.1">1.1–2.1 mm</quantity>
wide; ovate; green or yellow, with yellow margins; surface hairy, with simple and few branched hairs (2 rays: 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFD726B9D3D215AA5" box="[759,778,1728,1751]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14792" name="Yale University" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Herbarium">Y</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFF536BBC3EC65A8B" box="[214,237,1761,1785]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
); margins glabrous; apices obtuse or acute. Petals 4; 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFF416A5E3F6E5B68" box="[196,325,1795,1819]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="4.55" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="3.8">3.8–5.3 mm</quantity>
long; 2.0– 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFE3F6A5E3C265B68" box="[442,525,1795,1819]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
wide; obovate; slightly lobed or undulating; yellow. Androecium with 6 stamens and 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFF5D6A1A3F775B2C" box="[216,348,1863,1887]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="0.5" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.6 mm</quantity>
long anthers. Gynoecium with 1 style and 1 stigma. Fruit a silique; 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFD846A343C415BF2" box="[513,618,1897,1921]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="4.0">4–11 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFD3D6A343EF95BD0" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="4.4" valueMin="2.3">2.3–4.4 mm</quantity>
wide; ovate or lanceolate; flattened; green or purple; hairy, with simple and branched hairs (2 rays: 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFD216AF03C935BB6" box="[676,696,1965,1988]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14792" name="Yale University" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Herbarium">Y</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFD416AF03CFC5BB6" box="[708,727,1965,1988]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
, and 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFF2C6A923E975B95" box="[169,188,1999,2023]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">T</collectionCode>
). Styles persisting in fruits 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFE756A923C585B94" box="[496,627,1999,2023]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.7 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFD3F6A923EFF547A" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.4 mm</quantity>
wide. Stigmas 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFE036AAC3C27547A" box="[390,524,2033,2057]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.9 mm</quantity>
wide; distinctly larger than the styles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F20E36F7A267FFBEFCCA6DFC3A2B5E82" blockId="11.[809,1421,160,752]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">
Among the yellow-flowered 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFB1A6DFD3B6E5CCA" box="[1183,1349,160,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFB1A6DFD3ACE5CCA" box="[1183,1253,160,184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">Draba</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
present on Ellesmere Island (
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFBC56D9F3B6B5CAB" authority="Linnaeus, D." authorityName="Linnaeus, D." box="[1088,1344,194,218]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpina">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFBC56D9F3A835CA8" box="[1088,1192,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. alpina</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFAA36D9F3B6B5CAB" box="[1318,1344,194,217]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFACC6D9F3D755C89" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">arcto- gena</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFCEA6DBE3DA85C89" box="[879,899,227,251]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15670" name="Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Herbarium">E</collectionCode>
. Ekman) 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFC696DB93A2B5C89" box="[1004,1024,228,251]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15670" name="Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" type="Herbarium">E</collectionCode>
. Ekman, 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFBEC6DB93B4D5C89" authority="Hooker" authorityName="Hooker" box="[1129,1382,227,251]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micropetala">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFBEC6DB93B265C89" box="[1129,1293,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. micropetala</emphasis>
Hooker
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFAF66DB93A9C5D6E" authority="R. Brown ex de Candolle" authorityName="de Candolle" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongata">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFAF66DB93DBC5D6E" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. oblongata</emphasis>
R. Brown ex de Candolle
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFB706C583BAF5D6E" box="[1269,1412,260,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauciflora">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFB706C583BAF5D6E" box="[1269,1412,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. pauciflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="96204B06A267FFBEFCAF6C7B3DC95D4C" author="Aiken SG &amp; Dallwitz MJ &amp; Consaul LL &amp; McJannet CL &amp; Boles RL &amp; Argus GW &amp; Gillett JM &amp; Scott PJ &amp; Elven R &amp; LeBlanc MC &amp; Gillespie LJ &amp; Brysting AK &amp; Solstad H &amp; Harris JG" box="[810,994,294,318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" refId="ref39312" refString="Aiken SG, Dallwitz MJ, Consaul LL, McJannet CL, Boles RL, Argus GW, Gillett JM, Scott PJ, Elven R, LeBlanc MC, Gillespie LJ, Brysting AK, Solstad H, Harris JG (2007) Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: descriptions, illustrations, identification, and information retrieval. CD-ROM, National Research Council of Canada Research Press, Ottawa, Canada. http: // nature. ca / aaflora / data. Accessed on: 2020 - 08 - 05." type="url" year="2007">Aiken et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<collectionCode id="94A0AE32A267FFBEFC6E6C7B3A035D4C" box="[1003,1064,294,318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">GBIF</collectionCode>
2020), 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFBF16C7A3B205D4C" box="[1140,1291,294,318]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corymbosa">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFBF16C7A3B205D4C" box="[1140,1291,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. corymbosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFAB86C7A3A7E5D2D" authority="Elven &amp; Al-Shebaz" authorityName="Elven &amp; Al-Shebaz" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simmonsii">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFAB86C7A3D595D2D" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. simmonsii</emphasis>
Elven &amp; Al-Shebaz
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by larger petals (
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFCFF6C343DFC5DF2" box="[890,983,361,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
wide; 
<bibRefCitation id="96204B06A267FFBEFBA66C343ACE5DF3" author="Aiken SG &amp; Dallwitz MJ &amp; Consaul LL &amp; McJannet CL &amp; Boles RL &amp; Argus GW &amp; Gillett JM &amp; Scott PJ &amp; Elven R &amp; LeBlanc MC &amp; Gillespie LJ &amp; Brysting AK &amp; Solstad H &amp; Harris JG" box="[1059,1253,361,385]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" refId="ref39312" refString="Aiken SG, Dallwitz MJ, Consaul LL, McJannet CL, Boles RL, Argus GW, Gillett JM, Scott PJ, Elven R, LeBlanc MC, Gillespie LJ, Brysting AK, Solstad H, Harris JG (2007) Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: descriptions, illustrations, identification, and information retrieval. CD-ROM, National Research Council of Canada Research Press, Ottawa, Canada. http: // nature. ca / aaflora / data. Accessed on: 2020 - 08 - 05." type="url" year="2007">Aiken et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
; Elven and Al- Shehbaz 2008; Garneau and Sabourin 2018). 
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFA986CD63D765DB1" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. corym- bosa</emphasis>
also has wider fruits (
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFBD56CF63AE55DB1" box="[1104,1230,427,451]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="4.3" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="3.1">3.1–5.5 mm</quantity>
wide) and longer styles persisting in fruits (0.4–1.0 mm long) compared to 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFCAC6CB23DA55E74" box="[809,910,494,518]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpina">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFCAC6CB23DA55E74" box="[809,910,494,518]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. alpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFC1E6CB23A165E74" box="[923,1085,494,518]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micropetala">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFC1E6CB23A165E74" box="[923,1085,494,518]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. micropetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFBF26CB23B205E74" box="[1143,1291,495,518]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFBF26CB23B2C5E74" box="[1143,1287,495,518]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simmonsii">D. simmonsii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which have 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFCAC6F4D3D805E55" box="[809,939,528,552]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8499999999999996" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="2.8499999999999996" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="1.9">1.9–3.8 mm</quantity>
wide fruits and 
<quantity id="35499B12A267FFBEFBEF6F523B215E55" box="[1130,1290,527,551]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="0.175" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.05">0.05–0.30 mm</quantity>
long styles (Elven and Al-Shehbaz 2008; 
<bibRefCitation id="96204B06A267FFBEFBFE6F6C3BA35E3B" author="Al-Shehbaz IA &amp; Windham MD &amp; Elven R" box="[1147,1416,561,585]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" pagination="269 - 347" refId="ref39540" refString="Al-Shehbaz IA, Windham MD, Elven R (2010 b) Draba Linnaeus. In: Flora of North America Editorial Committee (Ed.) Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 7 - Magnoliophyta: Salicaceae to Brassicaceae. Oxford University Press, New York, USA / Oxford, UK, 269 - 347." type="book chapter" year="2010">Al-Shehbaz et al. 2010b</bibRefCitation>
; Garneau and Sabourin 2018). 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFBF66F0E3B275E18" box="[1139,1292,594,618]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corymbosa">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFBF66F0E3B275E18" box="[1139,1292,594,618]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">D. corymbosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has mainly branched hairs on the abaxial leaf surface, whereas the other yellow-flowered 
<taxonomicName id="35B14D74A267FFBEFB9F6FC83A9F5EDF" box="[1050,1204,661,685]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Draba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="C0C5EAE5A267FFBEFB9F6FC83A4B5EDF" box="[1050,1120,661,685]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="192">Draba</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have simple or simple and branched hairs (Al-Shehbaz and Mulligan 2013; 
<bibRefCitation id="96204B06A267FFBEFCAE6F853DDE5E82" author="Saarela JM &amp; Sokoloff PC &amp; Gillespie LJ &amp; Bull RD &amp; Bennett BA" box="[811,1013,728,752]" pageId="11" pageNumber="192" pagination="1 - 330" refId="ref44308" refString="Saarela JM, Sokoloff PC, Gillespie LJ, Bull RD, Bennett BA, Pono- marenko S (2020) Vascular plants of Victoria Island (Northwest Territories and Nunavut, Canada): a specimen-based study of an Arctic flora. PhytoKeys 141: 1 - 330. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / phytokeys. 141.48810" type="journal article" year="2020">Saarela et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
